{
  "text": "The exposition follows closely [CITATION_1] . Let N be prime. By F := F N we denote {0, 1, . . . , N − 1}. Moreover, F * := F \\ {0}. We also put F := is a rank-1 lattice if for some g ∈ (F * ) d it admits a representation",
